'''火雞肉'''，肉品來源通常是[[馴化|馴化]]的[[火雞|火雞]]。[[火雞肉|火雞肉]]不只是在[[感恩節|感恩節]]、[[耶誕節|耶誕節]]或[[跨年夜|跨年夜]]等特殊節日佔有文化上的重要性，平常日也是很受歡迎的禽肉食品。

== 製作與生產 ==
{{营养值|name=Turkey, breast, meat only, raw|carbs=0 g|fat=0.7 g|protein=24.6 g|kJ=465|sugars=0 g|fiber=0 g|thiamin_mg=0|riboflavin_mg=0.1|niacin_mg=6.6|pantothenic_mg=0.7|vitB6_mg=0.6|folate_ug=8|vitC_mg=0|calcium_mg=10|iron_mg=1.2|magnesium_mg=28|phosphorus_mg=206|potassium_mg=293|sodium_mg=49|zinc_mg=1.2|source=USDA Nutrient Database <ref>{{cite web|title=Turkey, fryer-roasters, breast, meat only, raw|url=http://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/poultry-products/858/2|publisher=USDA Nutrient Database|access-date=2016-12-06|archive-date=2020-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924132628/https://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/poultry-products/858/2|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}有整隻販售的火雞，也有將火雞切片或做成絞肉販售。冷凍全雞也很常見。火雞肉片常用於製作[[三明治|三明治]]或[[冷盤|冷盤]]；有時候可以用來代替雞肉。火雞絞肉與牛絞肉類似，商人常以火雞肉比[[牛肉|牛肉]]健康行銷火雞絞肉。大眾常認為如果烹調不當，火雞肉會比其它禽肉（如雞或鴨）乾澀。

[[野生火雞|野生火雞]]與養殖火雞其實是同一品種，但吃起來卻大不相同。大多數的肉屬於「紅肉」（即使雞胸也一樣），風味也比較強烈。季節也是影響雞肉風味因素，因為每個季節的糧食組成有差異，例如夏末的野生火雞會吃比較多的昆蟲，因此這個時期的野味較重。野生火雞主要以草和穀物為食，風味較溫和。較古老的馴養品種風味也不一樣。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.loc.gov/rr/scitech/mysteries/turkeymeat.html|title=Why do turkeys have dark and white meat?|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|date=|publisher=[[Library_of_Congress|Library of Congress]]|quote=|website=loc.gov|access-date=2015-06-06|archive-date=2019-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120072341/http://loc.gov/rr/scitech/mysteries/turkeymeat.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

火雞肉大多都經過食品加工。煙燻的火雞肉製成火雞肉火腿或火雞肉培根，大眾多認為比豬肉培根更健康。扭成螺旋狀的油炸火雞肉「turkey twizzlers」在2004年因主廚傑米‧奧利佛的倡導活動而聲名大噪，他在英國致力於將這類食物從學校午餐中去除。

火雞蛋不像[[雞蛋|雞蛋]]常見於市面上，因為對於整隻火雞的需求量較高，而火雞蛋的產量低於其它禽類（[[雞|雞]]、[[鴨|鴨]]或[[鵪鶉|鵪鶉]]）。一顆火雞蛋價格大約3.50[[美元|美元]]左右，幾乎是一打雞蛋的價錢。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.straightdope.com/columns/read/1262/why-cant-you-buy-turkey-eggs-in-stores|title=Why can't you buy turkey eggs in stores?|accessdate=2010-11-25|author=Cecil Adams|work=The Straight Dope|archive-date=2020-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811223523/https://www.straightdope.com/columns/read/1262/why-cant-you-buy-turkey-eggs-in-stores/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.discovery.com/videos/why-tell-me-why-turkey-eggs.html|title=Why? Tell Me Why!: Turkey Eggs|accessdate=2010-11-25|author=Kasey-Dee Gardner|date=2008-11-18|work=DiscoveryNews|archive-date=2012-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121127222323/http://news.discovery.com/videos/why-tell-me-why-turkey-eggs.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 文化傳統 ==
[[File:Thanksgiving_1918.jpg|缩略图]]結束後的感恩節大餐中享用火雞。]]
傳統上火雞是[[美國|美國]]和[[加拿大|加拿大]]感恩節，或其它地區[[耶誕大餐|耶誕大餐]]（常是填料火雞）的主菜<ref name="demystifying">{{cite web|url=http://www.mexconnect.com/articles/2122-demystifying-mole-m%C3%A9xico-s-national-dish|title=Demystifying Mole, México's National Dish|accessdate=2010-08-20|author=Karen Hursh Graber|date=2003-01-01|publisher=exConnect|archive-date=2019-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220231041/http://www.mexconnect.com/articles/2122-demystifying-mole-m%C3%A9xico-s-national-dish|dead-url=no}}</ref>。早在16世紀的[[英格蘭|英格蘭]]就有食用火雞的紀錄。20世紀之前，豬肋排是北美洲節日最常見的食物，因為通常在十一月宰殺。火雞原本在野外很常見，整年都可以吃得到，因此被視為日常菜餚，但豬肋排幾乎只有在感恩節至新年期間才吃得到。<ref>{{cite book|title=Mountain Cooking|last=Parris|first=John|publisher=Asheville Citizen-Times|year=1982|asin=B000UIRZVE}}</ref> 耶誕節吃火雞的傳統在17世紀傳遍英格蘭，<ref name="DAV">Davis, Karen (2001) [https://books.google.com/books?id=NxHN2RKmI3gC&pg=PA54 More than a meal: the turkey in history, myth, ritual, and reality] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NxHN2RKmI3gC&pg=PA54 |date=20190607210811 }} Lantern Books, 2001</ref> 當時的工人將其改為[[鵝肉|鵝肉]]，一直到[[維多利亞時代|維多利亞時代]]都是烤肉主流。<ref name="VCT">[http://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/England-History/VictorianChristmas.htm A Victorian Christmas] {{Wayback|url=http://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/England-History/VictorianChristmas.htm |date=20120130011530 }} ''Historic UK.com'' Retrieved December 26, 2010</ref>

2009年英國耶誕節當日的火雞消費量是 7,734,000隻。

搭配巧克力辣椒醬（mole sauce）的火雞被視為墨西哥國菜。<ref name="demystifying"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://travelfoodanddrink.com/north-america/mexico/ |title=Travel Food and Drink:  Explore Mexico |access-date=2016-12-06 |archive-date=2020-02-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217133034/http://travelfoodanddrink.com/north-america/mexico/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 烹調 ==
[[File:Hinduşka_qızartması.jpg|缩略图]]
新鮮或冷凍火雞都可以用於烹調；跟其他食物一樣，即使比較昂貴，偏好新鮮火雞的人還是比較多。節日期間，新鮮火雞的需求量很高，如果沒有事先預訂恐怕很難買到。大隻的冷凍火雞通常做為食用火雞，最困難的是解凍：要花好幾天才能解凍一隻普通大小的火雞。

火雞通常用烤箱烘烤數小時，趁烤的時候準備其它餐點。有時候為了促進風味和濕潤度，火雞會先鹽漬再烤。較高的溫度才能使紅肉的肌紅蛋白變性（白肉的肌紅蛋白含量極低），因此全熟的紅肉通常都比較乾澀。鹽漬可以使紅肉就算煮熟了也不會那麼乾。有時候火雞會在腿骨或其它骨頭末端加上裝飾（紙製裝飾或稱「booties」）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eatturkey.com/faq/faq.cgi/2/#44|title=FAQs|accessdate=2011-10-18|publisher=Eatturkey.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930151442/http://www.eatturkey.com/faq/faq.cgi/2/#44|archivedate=2011-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://zidbits.com/2010/11/does-turkey-really-make-you-sleepy-after-eating/|title=Does Turkey Really Make You Sleepy After Eating?|access-date=2016-12-06|archive-date=2020-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201141445/https://zidbits.com/2010/11/does-turkey-really-make-you-sleepy-after-eating/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

某些地區，特別是[[美國南部|美國南部]]會用火雞炸爐以油炸（通常用花生油）方式烹調火雞，火雞在油鍋裡炸30至45分鐘。油炸火雞也成為一種流行，但是必須要小心處理大量熱油，否則後果可能不堪設想。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ul.com/global/eng/pages/offerings/perspectives/consumer/productsafety/turkeys/|title=Product Safety Tips: Turkey Fryers|accessdate=2007-12-21|publisher=[[Underwriters_Laboratories|Underwriters Laboratories]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425105902/http://www.ul.com/global/eng/pages/offerings/perspectives/consumer/productsafety/turkeys/|archive-date=2009-04-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>另外當地有把整隻去骨的雞鴨和填入火雞腹中一同烤製的食法，稱為[[火鴨雞|火鴨雞]]。

=== 營養價值 ===
[[file:Thanksgiving_Turkey.jpg|缩略图]]
火雞肉的蛋白質含量較其它肉類高。<ref name="turkeyprotein">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=566WYqlegVUC&pg=PA43&dq=chicken+turkey+protein+100+grams&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5gS2UYfaBIXG4AOE14HgBg&ved=0CGEQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=chicken%20turkey%20protein%20100%20grams&f=false|title=Proteins for a Healthy Body|last=Royston|first=Angela|publisher=Capstone Classroom|year=2009|page=43|access-date=2016-12-06|archive-date=2019-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190602080851/https://books.google.com/books?id=566WYqlegVUC&pg=PA43&dq=chicken+turkey+protein+100+grams&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5gS2UYfaBIXG4AOE14HgBg&ved=0CGEQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=chicken%20turkey%20protein%20100%20grams&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>一般都認為火雞的白肉比紅肉更健康，因為白肉飽和脂肪含量低，但其實營養差異不大。人們常說火雞肉會讓人昏昏欲睡，其實節日大餐的餐點常見大份量的碳水化合物、脂肪和酒精，再加上輕鬆的氣氛都是造成飯後嗜睡的因素，這遠比火雞肉中的[[色胺酸|色胺酸]]能造成影響大得多。<ref name="sleepyturkey">{{cite web|url=http://chemistry.about.com/library/weekly/aa110402a.htm|title=Does eating turkey make you sleepy?|accessdate=2005-05-11|work=About.com|archive-date=2006-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060706204315/http://chemistry.about.com/library/weekly/aa110402a.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="sleepyturkey2">{{cite web|url=http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2006/thanksgiving.html|title=Researcher talks turkey on Thanksgiving dinner droop|accessdate=2006-11-21|work=Massachusetts Institute of Technology News Office|archive-date=2013-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130723035525/http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2006/thanksgiving.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 第二次世界大戰後，進口的便宜火雞屁股，在[[薩摩亞|薩摩亞]]開始流行。 但是這個部位太肥，造成太平洋地區的肥胖率提高。為打擊肥胖，2007至2013年間禁止進口火雞屁股，此後為了符合世界貿易組織的要求，火雞屁股才重回薩摩亞市場。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/templates/transcript/transcript.php?storyId=182568333|title=Samoans Await The Return Of The Tasty Turkey Tail|accessdate=2014-09-27|date=2013-05-09|work=NPR.org|archive-date=2018-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830004920/https://www.npr.org/templates/transcript/transcript.php?storyId=182568